<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-668-031  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 668 031.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  April 10 1989 v3 n15 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>OMB to limit agencies' cross-servicing efforts. (Office ofManagement and Budget)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Casatelli, Christine.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Office of Management and Budget is beginning to blockgovernment agencies from providing computer services to otheragencies, or 'cross-servicing.' OMB disapproves of agenciesbecoming data processing entrepreneurs rather than public servantsand in particular does not want agencies to expand their computingresources solely to cross-service; client agencies should bear theburden of proving such a method is more efficient andcost-effective than going to the market.andP;  The OMB argues thatcross-servicing should be the province only of agencies withunique processing capabilities and at facilities with excesscomputing power.andP;  OMB has already prevented the Small BusinessAdministration from providing the Agriculture Department'sNational Computer Center with its excess computing capacity; theComputing Center has been directed to solicit commercial firms forthe job.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Office of Management and BudgetGovernment AgencyGovernment RegulationComputer ServicesNational GovernmentPolicy.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>